-- Australia shares seen sliding on global growth worries
-- 
-- Mon Jan 27, 2014 05:06PM EST
-- None



MELBOURNE, Jan 28 (Reuters) - Australian shares are set to open lower on Tuesday following a long weekend, catching up with losses offshore on worries about a slowdown in China's growth and a further paring of monetary stimulus by the U.S. Federal Reserve.

* Local share price index futures <YAPcm1> fell 0.8 percent to 5,118.0, a 122.9-point discount to the underlying S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO>. The benchmark slipped 0.4 percent last Friday, ending the week down 1.2 percent. * New Zealand's benchmark NZX 50 index <.NZ50> fell 0.3 percent to 4,839.9 in early trade. * U.S. stocks fell on Monday, with the Dow down for a fifth straight session and the S&P 500 index off for a third in a row on concern about the Federal Reserve's plans for withdrawing stimulus. * Copper hit its lowest in seven weeks on Monday, while gold fell around 1 percent. * Building materials group Boral Ltd <BLD.AX> said it expects to report a first half profit before one-offs of about A$90 million, up from A$52 million a year ago, thanks to strong volumes on major projects and cost-cutting benefits. [ID:nWNBS00AOM] * Perseus Mining <PRU.AX> reported a 6 percent rise in gold production from the previous quarter to 48,360 ounces. [ID:nWNBS00AOL]  ------------------ MARKET SNAPSHOT @ 2158 GMT ------------------ INSTRUMENT   LAST   PCT CHG   NET CHG S&P 500 <.SPX>   1,781.56-0.49%-8.730 USD/JPY <JPY=>   102.54   0.25% 0.260 10-YR US TSY YLD<US10YT=RR>  2.7479  -- 0.013 SPOT GOLD   <XAU=>   1,256.6  0.01% 0.160 US CRUDE<CLc1>   95.7-0.97%-0.940 DOW JONES   <.DJI>   15,837.88   -0.26%-41.23 ASIA ADRS   <.BKAS>  140.55  -0.83% -1.18 ---------------------------------------------------------------- * Wall St ends lower; S&P 500 extends losses for 3rd day  [.N]   * Oil loses $1 as emerging markets struggle, Fed weighs  [O/R]   * Gold falls 1 pct on U.S. Fed worries  [GOL/]   * Growth worries drag copper to 7-week low [MET/L]  DIARIES & DATA:  IPO diary & data  <AU/IPOMENU>  Asia earnings diary [ASIA/EQTY]  U.S. earnings diary  [RESF/US]  European diary   [WEU/EQTY]  Australia diary  [AU/DIARY] Wall Street Week Ahead   [.N/O]  Eurostocks Week Ahead  [.EU/O] ................................................................ For latest top breaking news across all ma